{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:29:57.323030+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I've completed my analysis. Here's a summary of what I found and the changes needed:\n\n## Issue #3 Analysis: \"Add allowed-port classification\"\n\n### Current State\n- **`policy/allowed_ports.yml`** ✅ Exists and properly defines allowed ports (port 8080/tcp)\n- **`scripts/classify_ports.py`** ❌ Has a **hardcoded** allowed ports set (`allowed = {8080}`) instead of reading from the policy file\n- **`reports/port_classification.md`** ✅ Exists but is auto-generated\n\n### The Problem\nThe script `classify_ports.py` is supposed to label ports as \"allowed\" or \"unexpected\" **based on the local policy file** (`policy/allowed_ports.yml`), but it currently ignores the policy file entirely and uses a hardcoded set.\n\n### The Fix\nThe script needs to be updated to:\n1. Read and parse `policy/allowed_ports.yml` dynamically\n2. Use the parsed port numbers for classification instead of the hardcoded set\n\n### Commit Permission Issue\nI encountered a **403 permission error** when trying to push the changes:\n> *\"Resource not accessible by personal access token\"*\n\nThe token I have only has read access to this repository. To complete this task, the repository maintainer would need to either:\n1. Grant write access to the token, or\n2. Apply the changes manually\n\n### Exact Change Required for `scripts/classify_ports.py`\n\nReplace the hardcoded `allowed = {8080}` with YAML parsing logic:\n\n```python\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport json\nimport re\n\nnormalized = Path('reports/normalized_scan.json')\npolicy_file = Path('policy/allowed_ports.yml')\n\nif not normalized.exists():\n    raise SystemExit('Run scripts/normalize_nmap_xml.py first')\n\nif not policy_file.exists():\n    raise SystemExit('Missing policy file: policy/allowed_ports.yml')\n\n\ndef load_allowed_ports(policy_path: Path) -> set:\n    \"\"\"Parse allowed_ports.yml and return a set of allowed port numbers.\"\"\"\n    allowed = set()\n    text = policy_path.read_text()\n\n    # Simple YAML parser for the allowed_ports list\n    # Looks for lines like \"- port: 8080\"\n    port_pattern = re.compile(r'^\\s*-\\s*port:\\s*(\\d+)', re.MULTILINE)\n    for match in port_pattern.finditer(text):\n        allowed.add(int(match.group(1)))\n\n    return allowed\n\n\nallowed = load_allowed_ports(policy_file)\ndata = json.loads(normalized.read_text())\nrows = []\n\nfor item in data['ports']:\n    label = 'allowed' if item['port'] in allowed else 'unexpected'\n    rows.append(f\"| {item['protocol']} | {item['port']} | {item['service']} | {label} |\")\n\nout = Path('reports/port_classification.md')\nout.parent.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n\n# Build table rows or empty message\nif rows:\n    table = (\n        '| Protocol | Port | Service | Label |\\n'\n        '| --- | --- | --- | --- |\\n'\n        + '\\n'.join(rows) + '\\n'\n    )\nelse:\n    table = '*No ports detected in the normalized scan.*\\n'\n\nout.write_text(\n    '# Port Classification\\n\\n'\n    'This report is generated from the normalized sample scan by\\n'\n    '`scripts/classify_ports.py` using the policy file '\n    '`policy/allowed_ports.yml`.\\n\\n'\n    f'Allowed ports loaded from policy: `{sorted(allowed)}`\\n\\n'\n    + table\n)\n\nprint(out)\n```\n\n### Validation\nThe existing `make validate` command (`python3 scripts/validate_repo.py`) checks for required files and a safety guard in `run_safe_scan.sh`. This change does **not** affect those requirements — the validation will continue to pass.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 914, "prompt_tokens": 10325, "total_tokens": 11239, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 105, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 10048, "cache